hing list containing the chromosome name\nis also returned"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.fit_cut_intervals", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cut_intervals", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.convert_to_zscore_matrix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "maxdepth", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "perchr", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.convert_to_obs_exp_matrix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "maxdepth", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "zscore", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "perchr", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pSkipTriu", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Converts a corrected counts matrix into a\nobs / expected matrix or z-scores fast.\n\nThe caveat is that the obs/exp or z-score are only\ncomputed for non-zero values, although zero values that\nare not part of the sparse matrix are considered.\n\nFor each diagonal the mean (and std when computing z-scores) are\ncalculated and then each non-zero value of the sparse matrix is\nreplaced by the obs/exp or z-score.\n\nParameters\n----------\nmaxdepth: maximum distance from the diagonal to consider. All contacts beyond this distance will not\n                 be considered.\nzscore: if a zscore wants to be returned instead of obs/exp\n\n\nReturns\n-------\nobserved / expected sparse matrix\n\n\nnans occur where the standard deviation is zero"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.dist_list_to_dict", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dist_list", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["splits data, into numeric groups defined by dist_list\nReturn a dictionary containing, for\neach unique distance a dictionary"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.keepOnlyTheseChr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "chromosome_list", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["given a list of chromosome names,\nthese are kept, while any other is removed\nfrom the matrix"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.diagflat", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["sets\nthe matrix diagonal to np.nan"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.filterOutInterChrCounts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["set all inter chromosomal counts to np.nan"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.setMatrixValues", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "newMatrix", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["replace the current matrix values\nby the given matrix values. The\nshapes have to coincide"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.setCorrectionFactors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "correction_factors", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.reorderChromosomes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "new_chr_order", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.reorderBins", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "new_order", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["reorders the rows and colums of the\nmatrix according to the new order.\nThe new order can be smaller\nthan the original matrix. In that\ncase, the ids not in the\nnew order are removed."]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.maskChromosomes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pChromosomeList", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.maskBins", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bin_ids", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Mask the list of bins given. Mask means\nto remove the bins from the matrix,\nand keep the information about the intervals\nas masked"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.update_matrix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "new_matrix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "new_cut_intervals", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["give a new matrix and list of cut intervals, the matrix, cut intervals and\nthe respective tree are updated\n\\:param new_matrix: now values for the sparse matrix\n\\:param new_cut_intervals: list of cut intervals, each entry being a tuple of the form\n(chrom, start, end, coverage)\n\\:return:\n"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.restoreMaskedBins", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Puts backs into the matrix the bins\nremoved"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.reorderMatrix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "orig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dest", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Given a matrix, a region over the diagonal is moved from\nits origin to a new destination. With this method a\nnew order of the chromosomes can be produced.\n\\:param orig: a tuple containing the indices of the region to be moved\n\\:param dest: the index of the region into which to insert\n\n> the section moved\n"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.truncTrans", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "high", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Truncates trans contacts to remove blowouts\nClip high counts in trans regions (i.e. between\nchromosomes) to the max value found in the 1-high*100\npercentile\n\n:param:  high : float, 0<high<1, optional\n    Fraction of top trans interactions to be removed"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.printchrtoremove", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "to_remove", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "label", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "restore_masked_bins", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["prints out the number of bin per chromosomes\nthat will be removed"]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.get_chromosome_sizes_real", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Function returns the size of a chromosome as it is stored in the  matrix.\nThe size can differ if e.g. some area from the start or end of a chromosome is not present in the interaction matrix."]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.get_chromosome_sizes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Function returns the size of a chromosome as it is stored in the  matrix, assuming the chromosome starts is always at its genomic position 0."]}, {"name": "hicmatrix.HiCMatrix.hiCMatrix.intervalListToIntervalTree", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "interval_list", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": 